Application Scenarios: E-commerce, manufacturing, retail, and more.

Implemented Functions:
 Provide data integration services for mainstream ERP vendors such as UFIDA, Kingdee, and Digiwin Software. Based on scenario-specific analysis, choose between encapsulated call integration or intermediate object integration to connect data across systems, enabling warehouse modeling, inbound/outbound management, in-warehouse operations, and warehouse visualization.

Application Value:
 Boost management efficiency while reducing human error and labor costs;
 Optimize inventory control: real-time inventory updates enable dynamic adjustment, reducing backlog and waste;
 Improve customer satisfaction: faster order processing and delivery, plus real-time inventory and order status lookup;
 Strengthen competitiveness: greater accuracy and efficiency lower operating costs and sharpen market positioning;
 Data-driven decisions: comprehensive real-time data and reports support more precise strategic planning;
 In summary, keep enterprise data flowing freely, prevent information silos from forming, and maximize the value of information systems, modules, and enterprise data.

Industry: Logistics

Key Challenges:
 Smudges, occlusions, and wrinkles on express waybills degrade recognition accuracy;
 Requires high-concurrency, high-speed sorting synchronized with cross-belt conveyors.

Key Technologies:
 Automatically identify barcode and three-segment code data on waybills of parcels moving at high speed on the conveyor belt. The barcode uniquely identifies each parcel, while the three-segment code specifies the sorting destination—together enabling fully automated parcel sorting;
 As parcels move along the conveyor, photoelectric sensors trigger industrial cameras to capture images;
 Captured images are preprocessed then processed through a pipeline of algorithms:
 Waybill Localization: locate the waybill region within the image;
 Text Detection: detect text areas within the waybill region to isolate the three-segment code and barcode;
 Text Recognition: recognize the character content of the three-segment code and barcode, then output the results.

Application Value:
 Lower labor costs;
 High efficiency and accuracy eliminate misjudgments caused by human eye fatigue;
 Fewer customer complaints;
 Stable long-term operation;
 Reduced material waste;
 Recognition rate up to 97%;
 Compatible with barcode systems from STO, YTO, ZTO, SF, and Yunda.

The airport security platform is built on the design philosophy of "Massive Scale, Intelligent Integration, Scenario-Driven" and delivers "One Platform, One Map, One Sky Network."

**"One Platform"** unifies access to diverse security equipment and integrates multiple systems, ensuring seamless interconnection and interoperability across all business systems;

**"One Map"** overlays security elements onto GIS maps for visual management;

**"One Sky Network"** leverages AI and digital technologies to make the security posture fully visible and decision-making data-driven, significantly strengthening the airport's comprehensive management and unified dispatch capabilities.

Core Functions:
 Staff attire compliance in the preparation area (chef uniforms, chef hats, masks);
 Rodent detection in preparation areas;
 Trash can lid detection;
 Fire detection (warehouse);
 People counting;
 Social distancing monitoring;
 Fire exit congestion detection;
 Left-item detection;
 Mobile alarm system (real-time alerts via WeChat Official Account);
 Monitoring dashboard.
